Construct triangles $OXZ$ and $OYZ$ so that $OX = 10,$ $OY = 3,$ $OZ = 7,$ $\angle YOZ = \theta$ and $\angle XOZ = 90^\circ - \theta.$  Then $\angle XOY = 90^\circ.$

Also, by the Law of Cosines on triangle $YOZ,$
\[YZ = \sqrt{3^2 + 7^2 - 2 \cdot 3 \cdot 7 \cos \theta} = \sqrt{58 - 42x}.\]By the Law of Cosines on triangle $XOZ,$
\begin{align*}
XZ &= \sqrt{7^2 + 10^2 - 2 \cdot 7 \cdot 10 \cos (90^\circ - \theta)} \\
